        "content": "<p>I'm interested in the following situation and couldn't find anything by googling, I hope someone knows a reference :)<br>\nConsider a category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> with two monads <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T, S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span> on it (and no kind of compatibility -- no distributive law, etc). There's a category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{T,S\\}\\mathrm{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span> of objects with independent <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-algebra and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span>-algebra structures, and morphisms that preserve both. There are forgetful functors <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>T</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U_T: \\{T,S\\}\\mathrm{Alg} \\to T\\mathrm{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10903em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>S</mi></msub><mo>:</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>S</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U_S: \\{T,S\\}\\mathrm{Alg} \\to S\\mathrm{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10903em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span> discarding one of the two structures.<br>\nI am interested in conditions for, say, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>U</mi><mi>T</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U_T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10903em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> to have a left adjoint -- the idea being that one can universally add an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span>-algebra structure on the carrier of a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-algebra, which does not need to be compatible with said <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-algebra, but does not “discard” it either...</p>",
        "id": 198663037,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590409800
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it obvious that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>T</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{T,S\\}\\mathrm{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span> has an initial object (assuming that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> does, but not that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span> preserve it)?<br>\nI think you probably want some local presentability/accessibility hypotheses; not sure exactly how much you need.</p>",
        "id": 198666191,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1590411809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess this will also be related to coproducts of monads.</p>",
        "id": 198667248,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1590412399
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276480\">Reid Barton</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category.20theory/topic/.22Relatively.20free.22.20algebra.20structure/near/198667248\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I guess this will also be related to coproducts of monads.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Ah yes, it looks like “indipendent <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span>-algebra structures” are the same as “algebra structures for the coproduct of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span>”! I had never heard of the coproduct of monads. Great, thanks, that gives me somewhere to start from.</p>",
        "id": 198668699,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590413275
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is a general existence theorem for colimits of monads in Section 27 of Kelly’s <a href=\"https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/FE2E25E4959E4D8B4DE721718E7F55EE/S0004972700006353a.pdf/unified_treatment_of_transfinite_constructions_for_free_algebras_free_monoids_colimits_associated_sheaves_and_so_on.pdf\">A unified treatment of transfinite constructions for free algebras, free monoids, colimits, associated sheaves, and so on</a>, though I find this paper hard to read.</p>",
        "id": 198866383,
        "sender_full_name": "Soichiro Fujii",
        "timestamp": 1590570143
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks Soichiro, I had indeed found that paper by Kelly and yes, it seems that noone has been able to make much of that section, until computer scientists became interested in computing some simpler cases in this century. Since then there's been a paper by Hyland, Plotkin and Power in 2002 on coproducts of <em>free</em> monads, one by Ghani and Uustalu in 2004 with a simple formula for the coproduct of <em>ideal</em> monads (which 'separate' as T = Id + T', with T' being the 'non-unit' part), and then a few generalisations of this formula, the most comprehensive being <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1409.3805\">this preprint</a> by Adámek.</p>\n<p>The basic idea seems to be the following: if the “image” of the unit of a monad can be 'separated' from the rest of it, so that TX decomposes as “X plus things with a non-trivial outer T-layer” (possibly in weaker ways than the case of ideal monads), and the same is true of S, then (T+S)X is going to be made of X, plus “things with (nontrivial) T-layers over S-layers over T-layers, etc”, plus “things with (nontrivial) S-layers over T-layers over S-layers, etc”.</p>",
        "id": 198873059,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590574841
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And this can be proved to exist by the usual fixpoint theorems, provided that you can give the “nontrivial part of T/ nontrivial part of S” enough structure (except for the case of ideal monads, they will not be endofunctors on the same category as T and S).</p>",
        "id": 198873371,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590575060
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anyway, to return to my original question, if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S+T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span> exists, because we have coproduct inclusions <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">S, T \\to S+T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span> in the category of monads on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span>, we can apply the general theorems on the existence of left adjoints to the 'relative forgetful functors' <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N\\mathrm{Alg} \\to M\\mathrm{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">A</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">l</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span></span></span></span> corresponding to monad morphisms <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M \\to N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 198873707,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590575332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"276363\">@Amar Hadzihasanovic</span> Has anyone written down more explicit formulas for <em>pushouts</em> of monads?</p>",
        "id": 199053602,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1590686799
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not that I've seen, I'm afraid. Adámek mentions that <em>absolute</em> coequalisers of monads are created by the forgetful functor to the category of endofunctors, which perhaps makes some pushouts more computable in combination with the coproduct formulas. But none of the articles I've seen treat other cases explicitly.</p>",
        "id": 199068672,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1590693361
    }
]